class Solution {
    public int hammingWeight(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n != 0) {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iteratively checks each bit of the input integer using bitwise operations. It counts the set bits and returns the total count. The time complexity is logarithmic because each iteration effectively halves the number of bits to check. The space complexity is constant as it only uses a few integer variables.

